Class LStack

java.lang.Object
  lib.LStack
All Implemented Interfaces:
Digestable
public class LStack
extends java.lang.Object
implements Digestable

this is a light weight alternate for Vector class, it is not threadsafe, and unlike vector, it has no compatibility problems with java 1.1.

Author:
ddyer

removeAtIndex

public long removeAtIndex(int i,
                          boolean shuffle)
remove the i'th element of the stack. This is done by moving the top element, so the order of items in the stack will change if items are removed from the middle.

Parameters:
i -
shuffle - if true, preserve the order of the other elements
